---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 13, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy · Viva Wellness Co."
  description="How Viva Wellness Co. collects, uses, and protects your information. Plain-language privacy practices for our concierge telehealth website."
>

  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="container legal-hero__inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">· Privacy</span>
      <h1 class="legal-hero__title">
        Your data, <span class="italic-display">your control.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Plain language. No dark patterns. Here is exactly what we collect, why,
        and how to opt out at any time.
      </p>
      <p class="legal-hero__updated">Last updated · {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-body">
    <div class="container legal-body__inner">

      <div class="legal-callout">
        <strong>The short version.</strong>
        We collect contact details when you fill out a form on this site, plus
        the answers you give to our protocol-match quiz. We use that information
        to email you our eBook, reply to your inquiry, and occasionally send you
        new articles. We never sell it. You can unsubscribe at any time.
      </div>

      <h2 class="legal-h">What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        From the <a href="/contact">contact page</a> and the home-page
        protocol-match quiz, we collect the information you give us: your name,
        email address, phone number (optional), the answers you choose in the
        quiz, and any free-text message you send.
      </p>
      <p>
        We also automatically receive limited technical information: which page
        referred you (the HTTP <em>Referer</em> header) and the campaign tags in
        your URL (UTM parameters). This is the same information any website
        receives by default. We use it to understand which articles and ads are
        useful so we can write more of what works.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> use analytics cookies on this site. We do
        not track you across other websites.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">How we use it</h2>
      <p>
        To deliver the Precision Hormone &amp; Peptide Therapy eBook to the
        email you provided, reply to questions you ask us, and follow up if
        Liliana wants to introduce a relevant new article or protocol. That is
        the entire scope of marketing communication from this website.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Service providers we use</h2>
      <ul class="legal-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Resend</strong> · sends our transactional email (eBook
          delivery and inquiry replies). Your name and email pass through their
          systems for that purpose.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare</strong> · hosts this website. They process the
          basic server logs and DDoS protection data that any web host needs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>GlossGenius</strong> · handles appointment booking and
          payments when you book a visit. They have their own privacy policy
          and we never see your full card details.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="legal-h">A note on health information (HIPAA)</h2>
      <p>
        This website does <strong>not</strong> collect protected health
        information (PHI). The quiz and contact forms are for marketing and
        lead intake only. Please do not share medical details, lab results,
        or symptoms through any form on this site.
      </p>
      <p>
        Once you become a patient, all clinical communication moves into our
        HIPAA-compliant patient portal (Charm Health). Lab orders, medication
        shipments, dose adjustments, and provider messaging happen there,
        never through this website or generic email. You receive our full
        <a href="/notice">Notice of Privacy Practices</a> during intake, which
        describes how PHI may be used and disclosed, and your rights as a
        patient.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you accidentally submit PHI through a form on this website, we
        delete it on receipt and ask you to re-submit through the patient
        portal once enrolled.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We do not use advertising trackers, social pixels, or session-replay
        tools. If and when we enable web analytics, it will be a
        privacy-respecting, cookieless tool (Plausible) that does not track
        you across other sites and does not collect personal data. No cookie
        banner is needed because there are no cookies to disclose.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        Marketing leads (name, email, phone, quiz answers, UTM tags, page
        referrer) are kept while you remain on our marketing list. If you
        unsubscribe or email us to request deletion, we remove your data
        within thirty days. Patient clinical records are retained as required
        by state medical-records law (typically seven years) and live in
        the patient portal, not on this website.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        For data this website collects (marketing leads, not PHI), you can:
      </p>
      <ul class="legal-list">
        <li>Ask what we have about you</li>
        <li>Correct it</li>
        <li>Delete it</li>
        <li>Receive a portable copy</li>
        <li>Opt out of all marketing email</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        For PHI held in your patient record, you have the rights described in
        our <a href="/notice">Notice of Privacy Practices</a>, including the
        right to access, amend, and request an accounting of disclosures of
        your PHI. Email
        <a href="mailto:info&#64;vivawellnessco.com">info&#64;vivawellnessco.com</a>
        to exercise any of these rights.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">State residents</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Texas residents.</strong> Under Texas Health and Safety Code
        Chapter 181 (Texas Medical Records Privacy Act / HB 300), you have
        protections around how your protected health information is used,
        disclosed, and accessed. The practice's full Notice of Privacy
        Practices, provided at intake, covers these.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Colorado residents.</strong> Under the Colorado Privacy Act
        (CPA), you have the right to access, correct, delete, and obtain a
        portable copy of your personal data, and to opt out of targeted
        advertising, sale of personal data, and profiling. We do not engage
        in targeted advertising, do not sell personal data, and do not
        profile users for automated decisions.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Florida residents.</strong> Under the Florida Digital Bill of
        Rights (effective July 2024), you have the right to access, correct,
        delete, and obtain a portable copy of personal information we hold
        about you, and to opt out of targeted advertising and sale of
        personal data. See above.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Breach notification</h2>
      <p>
        If a security incident affects your personal data, we will notify
        you and the appropriate regulators within the timeframes required
        by applicable law, including the FTC Health Breach Notification
        Rule and the state laws of Texas, Colorado, and Florida.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Email opt-out</h2>
      <p>
        Every email we send includes an unsubscribe link. You can also email
        <a href="mailto:info&#64;vivawellnessco.com">info&#64;vivawellnessco.com</a>
        and ask us to remove you from any list, and we will do so within one
        business day.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Children</h2>
      <p>
        Our services are for adults eighteen and older. We do not knowingly
        collect information from anyone under eighteen. If you believe a
        minor has submitted information through this site, email us and we
        will delete it promptly.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Updates</h2>
      <p>
        If we change how we handle information, we will update this page and
        revise the date at the top. Material changes get an email to anyone
        on our list.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Questions or complaints</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:info&#64;vivawellnessco.com">info&#64;vivawellnessco.com</a>
        or call <a href="tel:+17372107283">(737) 210-7283</a>. For HIPAA
        complaints, you may also contact the U.S. Department of Health and
        Human Services, Office for Civil Rights, at
        <a href="https://www.hhs.gov/ocr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">hhs.gov/ocr</a>.
        You will not be retaliated against for filing a complaint.
      </p>

      <p class="legal-foot">
        Viva Wellness Co. · 5900 Balcones Dr #19640, Austin, TX 78731
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-hero {
    padding: clamp(5rem, 11vw, 9rem) 0 clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .legal-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(800px 500px at 75% 0%, rgba(201, 120, 58, 0.14), transparent 65%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .legal-hero__inner { position: relative; max-width: 70ch; }
  .legal-hero__title {
    font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 6.5vw, 5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-hero__title .italic-display { color: var(--bronze-bright); }
  .legal-hero__updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mute);
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    padding-top: 1.2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .legal-body { padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem) 0 clamp(5rem, 10vw, 8rem); }
  .legal-body__inner { max-width: 70ch; margin: 0 auto; }

  .legal-callout {
    background: var(--ink-2);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--bronze);
    padding: 1.6rem 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(245, 241, 234, 0.9);
  }
  .legal-callout strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--bronze);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .legal-h {
    font-family: var(--font-display-italic);
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.6vw, 1.9rem);
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 2.8rem 0 1rem;
    color: var(--paper);
  }
  .legal-body p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(245, 241, 234, 0.85);
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    max-width: none;
  }
  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--bronze);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(201, 120, 58, 0.4);
    transition: color 200ms var(--ease), border-color 200ms var(--ease);
  }
  .legal-body a:hover {
    color: var(--bronze-bright);
    border-color: var(--bronze-bright);
  }
  .legal-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-list li {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    position: relative;
    color: rgba(245, 241, 234, 0.85);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .legal-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--bronze);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .legal-list strong { color: var(--paper); }

  .legal-foot {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--mute);
  }
</style>
